04/05/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- About 100 people gathered in Sarajevo on Tuesday (May 3rd) to mark the 19th anniversary of an attack against a Yugoslav National Army convoy, which left more than 40 soldiers dead.
They laid wreaths and lit candles in Hamdija Kresevljakovic Street (former Dobrovoljacka Street) where the attack took place.
Relatives of the victims again called on authorities to prosecute those responsible.
(Fena, BHRT, RTRS, Tanjug - 02/05/11)
